A payment processing workflow uses a Go Activity that calls an external payment API. The Activity has a `StartToCloseTimeout` of 30 seconds, a `HeartbeatTimeout` of 10 seconds, and a Retry Policy with `MaximumAttempts: 3`. The Activity successfully charges the customer, but the Worker crashes immediately after—before it can send `ActivityTaskCompleted` to the Temporal Service. On retry, the Activity runs again and charges the customer a second time. A teammate proposes fixing this by setting `MaximumAttempts: 1` to prevent retries entirely. What is the most correct analysis of this proposal?

```go
err = workflow.ExecuteActivity(ctx, ProcessPayment, activityOptions{
    StartToCloseTimeout: 30 * time.Second,
    HeartbeatTimeout:    10 * time.Second,
    RetryPolicy: &temporal.RetryPolicy{
        MaximumAttempts: 3,
    },
}, paymentParams).Get(ctx, nil)
```
